<subSubSection pageId="88" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="88.[790,1387,2292,2720]" pageId="88" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1908" box="[791,1034,2453,2482]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="146" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pelewensis">Pteropus pelewensis</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1273,2453,2482]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Pleropus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="88" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="griseus">griseus</taxonomicName>
species group. It is often regarded as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1822" box="[833,969,2538,2563]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="146" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mariannus">mariannus</taxonomicName>
, and subspecies yapensis is oft en conside idered a distinct distinct species i or subspe bspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1822" box="[883,1050,2617,2642]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="146" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="mariannus">P. mariannus</taxonomicName>
, however, recent genetic studies confirmed that it is a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1908" box="[791,916,2687,2720]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Pteropus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chiroptera" pageId="88" pageNumber="146" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pelewensis">pelewensis</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
